The name of Antoninus, ennobled by the virtues of Pius and Marcus, had been communicated by adoption to the diffolute Ve- rus, and by descent to the cruel Commodus. It became the ho- nourable appellation of the sons of Severus, was bestowed on young Diadumenianus, and at length prostituted to the infamy of the high priest of Emesa.
